# Incident Report – Case 03: Microsoft Account Phishing (Allowed Access)

## Time of Activity
05/25/2026 02:36:06.320

---

## Summary
A phishing email impersonating Microsoft security was successfully delivered and the malicious URL was accessed via firewall-allowed connection.

---

## Affected Entities
- Sender: no-reply@m1crosoftsupport.co
- Recipient: c.allen@thetrydaily.thm
- URL: https://m1crosoftsupport.co/login
- IP: 45.148.10.131

---

## Investigation Steps
- Checked domain reputation (typosquatted Microsoft domain)
- Correlated firewall logs for access confirmation
- Verified no credential submission or POST requests
- Reviewed browsing activity context

---

## Key Findings
- Typosquatted domain detected
- URL flagged malicious (1/93 vendors)
- Connection allowed but no further exploitation observed
- No credential exfiltration detected

---

## Conclusion
True Positive – phishing access attempt with no compromise

---

## Escalation Decision
Yes – due to successful access (not blocked)

---

## Remediation Actions
- Block domain at DNS/firewall
- User phishing awareness alert
- Monitor host for credential abuse attempts

